        <p><strong>phpBB</strong> is an Internet forum package written in the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('PHP', 'L'); ?>  scripting language.</p>
        <p>The name "phpBB" is an abbreviation of <strong>PHP Bulletin Board</strong>. Available under the GNU General Public License, phpBB is free and open source software.<p>
        <p>Features of phpBB include support for multiple database engines (<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('PostgreSQL', 'DB'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('SQLite', 'DB'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('MySQL', 'DB'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Oracle Database', 'DB'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft SQLServer', 'DB'); ?>), flat message structure (as opposed to threaded), hierarchical subforums, topic split / merge / lock, user groups, multiple attachments per post, full-text search, plugins and various notification options (e-mail, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Jabber', 'IT'); ?>  instant messaging, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('ATOM', 'WD'); ?>  feeds).</p>
